name: chicagotribune
text:
RT @John_Kass: How to drive politics out of your head before Christmas? Make my onion soup. It's all about the stock. My "What are you cooking for Christmas Dinner?"column @chicagotribune
https://t.co/NYe6J4IYjH

name: chicagotribune
text: The sandwich is made of two slices of Spam and Oreo cookies, topped with mayonnaise. https://t.co/cmNT0Sap7b

name: chicagotribune
text: “I ran the Chicago Marathon before, and this is like the marathon that never ends. Nurses are just running on fumes right now. I want to say that I’m numb. I don’t feel anything. I’m just going through the motions, just to get it done.” https://t.co/29CjFLqekl

name: chicagotribune
text: A week after the first shipment of Pfizer’s coronavirus vaccine arrived in Illinois, about 63,000 health care workers across the state have received their first of two doses of the immunization, Gov. J.B. Pritzker’s office said. https://t.co/BK19D2VmSi
